public static class Entity.State
extends java.lang.Object

"States" are synonymous with "Types of Entity". States are the core behavior manager of entities. They contain all the non changing values for each type of individual, whereas entities contain values that are different for everyone. States have access to any entity that is passed into it's methods, but normally they would only change the entity that they are embedded within. Entities do not draw themselves, rather, they call upon their own state to draw them, according to the entity's own individual characteristics. Entities also update themselves this way. They rely upon the state they link to in order to update themselves.
